    "how_to_grow": {
        "cultivation": "Grow under glass from corms planted in free-draining, loam-based compost in autumn. Grow on in full light and apply a weak, balanced, liquid fertiliser every three weeks before flowering. Dry off as the leaves die down in summer. Corms can also be bought in spring for planting outside for a one-off summer blooming, but after this would need to be grown under glass and allowed to winter grow. Plant corms 15cm (6in) deep",
        "propagation": "Propagate by seed sown as soon as ripe in autumn in a temperature of 13\u00b0C-15\u00b0C (55\u00b0F-59\u00b0F). Remove offsets when the corms are dormant in autumn and pot into equal parts loam-based compost and sharp sand",
